default 
defaultwe fully support the view expressed in L
defaultouise 
defaultEllman’s
default letter that the g
defaultovernment shou
defaultld analyse the impact of the electronic portal 
defaultbefore
default it considers whether or not to increase th
defaulte threshold.
default 
defaultIt is clear from defaultour evidence defaultabove that defaultthe number of bodily injury claidefaultms is not as high as was claimed by the car insurersdefault and therefore there idefaults no case for rushing into further legal changes until the facts and all the implications are much clearer.default&#xa0;
defaultFrom our own work, we know that people with genuine claims are often pressurised into accepting less compensation than they deserve by 
defaultinsurers and 
defaultlawyers acting for
default them
default. We attach as an appendix 
defaultthe 
defaultcase of
default Donald and Enid 
